  "text": "The OpenJDK/JDK security provider registration framework is implemented through a hierarchy of provider classes and supporting infrastructure. At the foundation is the abstract base class `java.security.Provider` (src/java.base/share/classes/java/security/Provider.java), which provides the core `putService()` method used by all providers to register cryptographic services and algorithms. The Provider.Service inner class encapsulates individual service implementations with metadata about type, algorithm name, and implementation class. Several major provider implementations extend Provider to register their algorithms: the `Sun` provider (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/provider/Sun.java) implements core security algorithms by delegating to SunEntries; the `SunRsaSign` provider (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/rsa/SunRsaSign.java) handles RSA signature operations using SunRsaSignEntries; the `SunJCE` provider (src/java.base/share/classes/com/sun/crypto/provider/SunJCE.java) provides cryptographic algorithms including AES, DES, and PBE; the `SunJSSE` provider (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/ssl/SunJSSE.java) supplies SSL/TLS factories and related services through its `registerAlgorithms()` method; and the `SunEC` provider (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/ec/SunEC.java) supplies elliptic curve algorithms through its `putEntries()` method. Supporting entry classes like SunEntries and SunRsaSignEntries define the specific services each provider offers. The lazy-loading mechanism is implemented through the `ProviderConfig` class (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/jca/ProviderConfig.java), which encapsulates provider name-to-class mapping and the `doLoadProvider()` method that defers provider instantiation until needed. The `Providers` utility class (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/jca/Providers.java) manages system-wide and thread-local provider lists, while `ProviderList` (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/jca/ProviderList.java) maintains the ordered list of configured providers and supports service lookup. The `GetInstance` class (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/jca/GetInstance.java) implements the service discovery mechanism that queries providers in order to find implementations via their `getService()` methods. The `VerificationProvider` (src/java.base/share/classes/sun/security/provider/VerificationProvider.java) serves as a fallback provider that registers algorithms only when Sun and SunRsaSign providers are unavailable."
}

